  "texts": [
    "Today, we understand that heat corresponds to the total energy within a mass: a kettle of boiling water has more heat than a thimble of boiling water.",
    "In contrast, temperature measures the average kinetic energy per molecular or atomic constituent: the temperature of boiling water is 100 °C in both the kettle and the thimble.",
    "The widespread practice of ascribing technical meanings to common words creates a particular challenge for research in the cognitive sciences.",
    "This literature is full of words like \"attention\" and \"distraction.\"",
    "When a psychologist writes terms like these, she does not necessarily mean the same thing as a lawyer or the person in the street."
  ],
